<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-74-0423 </DOCNO><TEXT>This manual is divided into four chapters: project organization, targetidentification, problem diagnosis, corrective action, and project evaluation.Following the text are substantial attachments containing sample forms,guidelines, and procedures that can be used in setting up and carryingout a comptrain effort. The goal of the comptrain project was to fieldtest a method for bringing small water and waste-water treatment plantsinto compliance with federal-state performance standards. The methodinvolves: intensive, on-site, plant-specific training in equipment operationand process control; community-specific management and financial training;and efforts to bring about policy and program changes leading to improvedplant performance.</TEXT></DOC>